snippet: The musicians of the Minnesota Orchestra agreed to a new contract on Tuesday with pay cuts less severe than management had initially sought.
abstract: Minnesota Orchestra agrees to new contract with smaller pay cuts than management had initially sought, ending one of most contentious labor battles in classical music world; labor relations dispute has left ensemble locked out since October 2012, led esteemed music director Osmo Vanska to resign, and forced cancellation of anticipated recording.
lead_paragraph: The musicians of the Minnesota Orchestra agreed to a new contract on Tuesday with pay cuts less severe than management had initially sought.

headline.main: Minnesota Orchestra Contract Ends Long Lockout
headline.print_headline: Minnesota Orchestra Contract Ends Long Lockout
